Now, MR.BLACK has dropped his latest triumph, a remix of ‚ÄòIn My Mind‚Äò that completely reshapes the original.

Differing somewhat from his signature sound, his remix of ‚ÄòIn My Mind‚Äô encompasses a range of influences that give the original a new lease of life. With a relentless bassline and an unforgiving beat, the remix is the perfect anthem to dominate any mainstage set. tracks.description:
Skytech returns to CYB3RPVNK with an end-of-summer big room gem in the form of new release "Expedition" that continues to impress and inspire us. The Polish DJ and producer never fails to prove his dynamic production abilities, always coming to the table with complex influences of progressive, electro, and bass that are seamlessly interwoven into every track. "Expedition" delivers a steadily building bassline that leads into a massive percussive drop, which is then polished off with energetic synths and a catchy vocal riff. All these elements combine to make "Expedition" a track that will light up dance floors around the globe. The new release follows Skytech's single "Touching Me" with DNF, also on CYB3RPVNK, from earlier this summer.

Mateusz Dziewulski - better known by his artist name Skytech - is already a household name in his home country of Poland, and the rest of the world is soon to follow. His name first appeared on the map when R3HAB discovered his original track "Tiger" and then helped Skytech to put final production touches on it, proving to be a winning team after "Tiger" skyrocketed to millions of streams on all platforms. Since then, the two have worked on numerous tracks together via the CYB3RPVNK imprint, such as "Fuego," "What You Do," "Hyperspace," "Starflight," and more, fusing their sounds to make music that is club and festival-friendly while never sacrificing substance and soul. Since then, Skytech has been touring around the world, increasing his global footprint with every electrifying live performance. In 2017, he was the most-streamed Polish act on Spotify and debuted at Tomorrowland, while in 2018 he came in a close second on the Polish Spotify charts right after Frideric Chopin. Follow Skytech and the rest of CYB3RPVNK's talented crew to see what they are up to
tracks.title: Skytech - Expedition

tracks.description:
Premiered on Trap Nation - https://youtu.be/d8ErxFasiJo

Extremely excited to welcome T-Mass and LZRD on our outlet! 
We've been following both of these talented artists for years, making incredible collaborations such as their remixes of "It's All On U", "New York City", "Break Through the Silence" and their own singles and remixes. 
We can proudly say that they are both on our favorite artists list and have been a huge influence in our taste in music and the reason why we fell in love with this genre.

T-Mass and LZRD have been known in the industry as artists who could remix anything and make it sound perfect! 
Both have remixes and singles that have been played over a million times on this platform and YouTube.
Being featured on Trap Nation and Trap City more times then we can count on our fingers and toes combined and have been successfully building their individual brands to represent their sound and uniqueness to the fullest extent.

It's been 2 years since they released their remix of "It's All On U" by ILLENIUM, hitting over 32 million plays on Trap Nation, it has helped build their fanbase all across the world!
Our eyes lit up when they first sent this over and we cannot describe the feeling and overwhelming happiness that hit us when we heard this amazing track! 
Keeping the emotions of the original yet putting so much hype and tension behind the lyrics, dropping not 1 but 3 different drops that completely take over our senses and light our brain on fire, T-Mass and LZRD remind us who truly rules this game!

In essence Bloodstream is a song about the feelings of love and infatuation and how these emotions can sometimes become so strong they take over you. When it feels like every little thing in your daily life becomes something you associate with someone or when you are alone it feels like that person is right there with you. They never leave your thoughts to the point it feels like they are inside of you.

tracks.description:
Free Download: https://www.toneden.io/savoyband/post/up-all-night

We've been growing tired of the kind of stagnant arrangement in lots of songs coming out in electronic music lately. So many songs are so predictable... and we never liked predictability - especially in art and music. This is one of our longest songs we've ever put out, and we considered making it two separate pieces, but we ended up loving the flow from section to section and the journey that it took us on. This isn't necessarily a banger or anything like that - just the vibe we were in at the time which was a deep, soulful exploration of lots of our influences all converged as one into something new.

tracks.description:
Free Download: https://www.toneden.io/savoyband/post/up-all-night

We've been growing tired of the kind of stagnant arrangement in lots of songs coming out in electronic music lately. So many songs are so predictable... and we never liked predictability - especially in art and music. This is one of our longest songs we've ever put out, and we considered making it two separate pieces, but we ended up loving the flow from section to section and the journey that it took us on. This isn't necessarily a banger or anything like that - just the vibe we were in at the time which was a deep, soulful exploration of lots of our influences all converged as one into something new.

tracks.description:
Free Download - http://edmlead.net/gate/downforanythingjagsyvosairemix 

Hello VXII Family.
Finally we are able to release this beautiful masterpiece, done by Jagsy who previously released Somebody with us and Vosai who is a super exciting and talented producer!

Jagsy and Vosai are on our list of favorite upcoming producers and words cannot describe how awesome it feels to release their remixes and support them!
The festival and summer vibes we are getting from this one is insane, using KARRA's beautiful vocals, chopping them and putting them in the drop, adding that siren in there to add to the hype this track creates and finally the huge kicks and bass that were used, it all creates such an impacting remix. we are too proud to be able to welcome Jagsy back and welcome Vosai in with open arms to our collective!

tracks.description:
Stream/Download my debut album 'Places We Don't Know': http://lnk.to/placeswedontknow

Feels incredible to be releasing my Debut Album, it's been such a long process and such a long challenge it kind of felt like this day would never come, but it did.

Conceptually the album is about romanticizing a naive world view. That naiveness and ignorance is something to be cherished. There's something really beautiful about the perfect worldview you have as a kid, that the world is harmless, beautiful and good. The more you learn and experience though the more you realise everything isn't perfect. So the less you know the more beautiful it is, it's the things we haven't done, the places we don't know, that have this unquestionable beauty to it. it's this world i'm trying to mirror with my album, the one that stays in your imagination.

Musically i knew i wanted to do a sonic representation of the concept, blending worldly sounds with small bedroom type samples and soundscapes. I really loved the idea of those two polarizing things being the two main factors that would lay the ground for the album. 

- Carl üíñ

tracks.description:
Zedd, Maren Morris, Grey - The Middle

We worked really hard on this record to get it just right and it feels great to be able to finally share it with everyone. It was super fun working with Maren because she is clearly an amazing singer and very talented musician.  And, I always love working with Grey because we push ourselves to make the best music possible and the end result is incredible. - Zedd
 
I met Zedd in Nashville several weeks ago when he came to town to record my vocal for ‚ÄúThe Middle‚Äù. My fans know that my sounds is reflective of my many influences as a songwriter and artist and I think they‚Äôll be ecstatic to hear this collaboration with him and Grey! - Maren Morris
 
Some songs come really quickly and naturally, but for a while there it seemed like this song didn‚Äôt want to come out. We ran into obstacle after obstacle, but we kept fighting for it because we knew this song was special. This is also our first time working with a country singer, and the different styles ended up fitting perfectly! SO glad that we can finally share this one with you, so enjoy! - Grey

fitting perfectly! SO glad that we can finally share this one with you, so enjoy! - Grey

Written on the way back from a road-trip celebrating their coming of age, ‚ÄúSLOW‚Äù is the debut EP of duo Lucas Mokrani and Claire Lengaigne. Linked by the spirit of evasion and spiritual elevation, these songs find their roots from the band's time into the wild. An introspection of the world, a quest for this moment of transcendence, dancing and chanting over minimal and elegant production. A poetic journey laying out the base of what‚Äôs to come from SAAVAN.

big shoutout to The Chainsmokers for incorporating this remix into their performance on SNL: https://tinyurl.com/chainsmokerssnl

I typically try not to follow the wave of producers who take a shot at remixing every @thechainsmokers track that gets released, but I felt this song was different than their usual and decided to put my own spin on it

the original grew on me a ton and after I started working on this I realized it was going to be one of my favourite releases. this remix grew a life of it's own but I feel it still keeps the integrity of the original.

Featured on The Chainsmokers: Nice Hair 36

Hey guys!

I can't thank you enough for the incredible support you've given my last track "Coconuts", it has really been truly touching to me. Onto my next project! I'm really grateful to Alex & Drew AKA The Chainsmokers for letting me remix this song as it's probably my favorite vocal from the album. I really hope you guys like it and play it out and like and repost it!

tracks.description:
Donate & Download: GravitasRecordings.lnk.to/freefallBH

‚ÄúFreefall‚Äù, the newest collaborative project from the noteworthy team of producer Au5 and vocalist Cristina Soto, is available now on Gravitas Music. Each song on the four track EP has a way of being concurrently uplifting and ferocious, stirring a range of emotional response. The duo‚Äôs obvious talents interplay effortlessly; Au5‚Äôs superb songwriting establishes the ideal foundation for Cristina‚Äôs luscious yet poignant lyrical splendor, culminating in a whole greater than the sum of its parts.

Like a prelude for a winter dreamland, the album begins with the title track‚Äôs blissful, orchestral introduction before morphing into a hard-hitting electro anthem. Next, ‚ÄúShock Diamond‚Äù forges ahead with a midtempo-turned-DnB affair, sporting impeccable sound design and vocal hooks sure to haunt your brain for days to come. The EP wraps up with the vividly powerful ‚ÄúEmergence‚Äù, quickly followed by an Au5 remix of the tune which takes the assailing original and dials it back for a more subdued, cinematic interpretation.

tracks.description:
A few months ago NGHTMRE reached out to me and asked if I'd be willing to remix his song 'Frontlines' with Zeds Dead.  I was hesitant, as I really liked the original and I'm a firm believer in leaving great songs as they are.  However, I told myself that I would do my best to *change* the nature of the song, rather than try to better it.  My goal was to produce a piece with a lot of emotion as well as energy - something that would make you happy as well as get you going.  I think this remix nails that concept, and I'm super excited to share it with you all! ‚öô

tracks.description:
I wrote this song with Yeah Boy at his parents house, in Adelaide, while I was touring Australia 2 years ago. I'm very excited to release it today, after spending months perfecting every little sound / melody! 

This song is out on my label BLUME, which means all of the proceeds from streams & sales will go to charity. Last year we raised $200,000 for Pencils of Promise, and 7 new schools will be built in South America from that fundraising by September 2017. Our next goal is to raise $30,000 for the ACLU, and this song will help contribute to that goal :) Once we've raised that, I wanna let you guys decide what charity we give to next! Much Love & Thanks for always supporting - J

tracks.description:
The first time I saw Adventure Club was September 27, 2012 at the first Counterpoint festival. I remember being instantly blown away by their performance, so much so that when I got home I went through their entire discography and I've been listening to them ever since. 
Flash forward to March 13th, 2015 when I got the opportunity to open for them in Charlotte. They came out of the green room to the stage, Leighton grabs me, turns me around and tells me I'm killin it! As you can imagine, that was yet another moment that left me in shock. 
To say that I am thankful for their friendship and support is understatement. These guys had no reason to support a little guy like me. I wasn't even good at producing back then, yet for some reason they did. And because of it, my drive to succeed multiplied. 
So when they gave me an opportunity to remix one of their tracks, there was no way I was going to disappoint them. I worked so hard on this track and I am unbelievably proud of the out come.
tracks.title: Adventure Club - Breathe Ft. SONDAR (Ra Remix)

tracks.description: ‚ÄúMake It Drop‚Äù is a representation of some of the more high energy styles of trap and beat music that I play out in my sets. I combined some of my favorite elements of vocal based beat music in the first drop, then went as high energy as I could take the piece on the second drop. I often find myself only playing the first drop in a club scenario, or only play the second drop in a festival set - the track is a great representation of the different boundaries of the Dr. Fresch brand in a live sense.

tracks.description: ‚ÄúMake It Drop‚Äù is a representation of some of the more high energy styles of trap and beat music that I play out in my sets. I combined some of my favorite elements of vocal based beat music in the first drop, then went as high energy as I could take the piece on the second drop. I often find myself only playing the first drop in a club scenario, or only play the second drop in a festival set - the track is a great representation of the different boundaries of the Dr. Fresch brand in a live sense.

tracks.description:
Without A Trace

 I ran into Valentin at HARD Day of The Dead, he was visiting LA and mentioned to me that he would be back in town for a while hanging. So we made some plans to mess around in the studio, no huge expectations or anything, but an opportunity to mess around with some beats! I think that our personalities and our curiosity for each others process made all of this a really natural feeling collaboration. We spent a lot of time working but we also ended up taking breaks here and there to show each other techniques, listen to music etc.. It really was a perfect example of the way I love to work on collaborative projects and am really proud of what we came up with for this!
This is off my remix album ALT CLASSIC that drops on Friday, May 13th.

tracks.description:
"I've been in love with Destructo's 'Techno' since the first time I heard it - I think midtempo electro and deeper indie dance are taking off, and I wanted to give the original my own rework. I liked how Destructo grabbed the sample from Eminem's 'Without Me', and decided to use more of that sample to build the song around. I kept the tempo at 112BPM, but decided to get more complex and weird with my bass arrangement - I hope my Fresch Fam love this remix as much as I do!"

Thank you all for the birthday wishes!! To celebrate you can download my new track "Blackout" as a free download!
Spotify: http://hwl.dj/BlackoutSpotify
Wallpapers: http://hwl.dj/BlackoutWallpaper

To celebrate his birthday and kick off a brand new year, Hardwell releases his much-hyped track ‚ÄòBlackout‚Äô. Loaded with towering drops, a beat heavy rhythm, and his trademark arena filling sound, ‚ÄòBlackout‚Äô begins the year with typical confidence and style from the Dutch superstar. After an outstanding 2015 Hardwell now looks to the future, enhancing his sound with new ideas and a forward thinking attitude. Available as a free download, ‚ÄòBlackout‚Äô has already set the bar that others will reach for in 2016. 

A percussive crescendo builds before exploding into a maelstrom of synths and hard hitting beats, carrying on where previous smash hit single ‚ÄòMad World‚Äô and Armin van Buuren collaboration ‚ÄòOff the hook‚Äô left off. Punctuated by a breathtaking euphoric breakdown, ‚ÄòBlackout‚Äô is the combination of a number of ideas, all stitched together seamlessly and assembled to perfection. 

After his recent record breaking United We Are Foundation event in Mumbai, Hardwell is set to further dominate the scene in 2016, branching out in terms of both musicality and live show spectacle. With Blackout he celebrates his birthday, but simultaneously demonstrates that with a brand New Year comes a brand new set of ideas and possibilities. ‚ÄòBlackout‚Äô is available as a free download, and will be available across streaming platforms the same day.

tracks.description:
Bassjackers - F*CK (Dimitri Vegas & Like Mike Edit) OUT NOW Grab your copy here: http://lnk.to/BassjackersFCK

Dimitri Vegas & Like Mike give their take on Bassjacker‚Äôs infamous ‚ÄòF*CK‚Äô

Smash The House‚Äôs head honcho‚Äôs Dimitri Vegas & Like Mike are always prepared to push the boundaries of dance music, and their edit of Bassjacker‚Äôs ‚ÄòF*CK‚Äô is no exception. Bassjackers are no stranger to creating dancefloor anthems themselves such as ‚ÄúBring That Beat‚Äù, ‚ÄúMarco Polo‚Äù, ‚ÄúRough‚Äù and many more. With Dimitri Vegas & Like Mike following on from their Beatport #1 track ‚ÄòMelody‚Äô on their own colossal Smash The House imprint, you can guarantee that this combination of two acts in such demand will only result in one outcome; a dancefloor bomb.
The bouncy bass, glitchy beat and stop-start synth give the track a jacking feel and provide the groove, but it is the cheeky vocal that sets the track apart. The lyrics, from DJ Yoeri‚Äôs original ‚ÄòFuck On Cocaine‚Äô, released in the midst of rave in 2001, are a throwback to the hedonistic reputation of dance music in years gone by. The growling bassline combines well with the vocal in the breakdown to set an ominous tone, which is switched up later in the track, with an epic ensemble of melodies and harmonies in the latter part creating a memorable contrast. The pounding kick that is introduced in the drop establishes the track as a peak-time, no-frills club banger that is sure to set fire to dancefloors across the world.
Bassjackers are a one-of-a-kind DJ-duo, who have made an enormous rise to the top these last years. The numerous collaborations with other artists and even remixes for A-list artists only confirm their status as dancefloor masters.
Dimitri Vegas & Like Mike have truly established themselves at the top of the list of the world‚Äôs DJ‚Äôs. ‚ÄòF*CK‚Äô is another track fresh off the relentless production line of dancefloor anthems, and will be heard at festivals and clubs the world over for a long time to come. Get your copy May 23rd via Smash The House!
tracks.title: Bassjackers - F*CK (Dimitri Vegas & Like Mike Edit) OUT NOW

The first time Martin heard this song on the radio, he called me (Tristan) up and was like, "you HAVE to hear this new song by Alessia Cara! It has this dope 'ay ay ay ahhh' vocal chant in the chorus!" Right away, we thought about how awesome it would be to remix it. Then about a week later, our manager emailed us the track (without knowing how much we liked it) and asked us if we wanted to take a stab at it. No brainer.

Anyways, we had so much fun making this remix! We made a crazy vocal chop in the drop, I played a little guitar, and it was our first time working with a rap. Hope you guys like it, and if you do, PLEASE give it a heart on HypeM. Thanks!

tracks.description:
<3 on HypeM: http://bit.ly/IsItLove_HypeM

HEY HEY -

I'm back to try and make your day more funky! Firstly, I can't say enough how much I appreciate all the support and love that you all gave me for 'Get It On'. It felt like a dream, and still feels like a dream, take a such a risk and for everyone to be on my side, and embrace it, so thank you guys!

So a little about this tune. Justin and I tour a lot together, and he was one of the first DJs I went on the road with - he's given me so much insight on the industry from the musical side to the business side, and I'm grateful to have had his support these past few years. We were playing in VA together, and I showed him Get It On, and he absolutely LOVED it, and soon after shot me over the Is It Love stems. I got to work, and made what I think is some funky sex music. The breakdowns sensual, but the drop has those Jenaux guitars and funk synths, breakbeat kick/snare rhythms. 

Anyway, really hope you guys are feeling it, all the proceeds from streaming and downloads go to Pencils of Promise, an incredible charity that helps build schools in developing countries.

Much love,

Eugene

tracks.description:
https://direct.lnk.to/Lark


--
I wrote Lark in April of 2015 after waking up in the morning to find a meadowlark had found a temporary home on the outside of my bedroom window. So for about 3 or 4 days I heard the little 4 note melody sung by this bird. I could not get it out of my head so I wrote this song around it. Lets just hope the bird doesn't hear it and report it for copyright infringement.  ;)

Huge shouts to Muzzy for sending me a cool drum sound for this song.

Is It Love? We think so. 3LAU has just released "Is It Love (REMIXED)" following the early success of his latest single ‚ÄòIs It Love‚Äô and the debut of his new not-for-profit record label, Blume. 3LAU has teamed up with producer/dj heavy hitters Arty, Sultan + Shepard, Jenaux and Justin Caruso to serve up a 4-track remix package that‚Äôs sure to be a hit for the summer. Each producer brings their own unique approach to the record, creating a musical journey that will satisfy your earbuds and leave you wanting more.
All of Blume ºs proceeds from sales & streams will be donated to Pencils of Promise, a charity foundation with the purpose of building schools in developing countries. You can support the EP by downloading and streaming at the links below.

tracks.description:
<3 on HypeM: http://bit.ly/IsItLove_HypeM

HEY HEY -

I'm back to try and make your day more funky! Firstly, I can't say enough how much I appreciate all the support and love that you all gave me for 'Get It On'. It felt like a dream, and still feels like a dream, take a such a risk and for everyone to be on my side, and embrace it, so thank you guys!

So a little about this tune. Justin and I tour a lot together, and he was one of the first DJs I went on the road with - he's given me so much insight on the industry from the musical side to the business side, and I'm grateful to have had his support these past few years. We were playing in VA together, and I showed him Get It On, and he absolutely LOVED it, and soon after shot me over the Is It Love stems. I got to work, and made what I think is some funky sex music. The breakdowns sensual, but the drop has those Jenaux guitars and funk synths, breakbeat kick/snare rhythms. 

Anyway, really hope you guys are feeling it, all the proceeds from streaming and downloads go to Pencils of Promise, an incredible charity that helps build schools in developing countries.

Much love,

Eugene

"Ben and I have been talking about collabing forever, and agreed that when we did it had to be the perfect representation of G-House, in its highest form. I'm so happy with how the track turned out, it's been destroying in my sets lately and think we accomplished exactly we set out to do... hopefully we get some fuckin' thanks for it." - Dr. Fresch

"This collab with Tony has been a long time coming, and we both agreed when the right idea came along we had to execute it precisely. Both with a west coast influence in music we knew the Hello Vocals would settle nicely into a proper G-House track. SPOTIFY, ITUNES, & APPLE MUSIC: smarturl.it/IATEremixes

i'm proud to introduce my first Zoo Mix, my reinterpretation of my own track as if it's gone wild and had the energy turnt way up. whenever i write a song, there are a lot of ideas that never make it to the actual track, and especially so on Closer... coming up with different ideas for a song has never been a problem for me, it's always choosing what stays and what goes that makes finishing songs difficult. so once i finally settled on a version of Closer that I loved, I knew there were a ton of different versions of it that existed in some alternate universe, and i knew i wanted to see what would happen if i started from scratch and went totally ham on it. so this is what came out, lots of wubs and womps and gross basses, something that bangs a little harder. hope you all love it... ENJOY!

tracks.description:
iTunes: http://bit.ly/runawayiT
Spotify: http://smarturl.it/runaway_s
Beatport Extended Mix: http://bit.ly/runawaybp
--
I've always been dedicated to trying new things, and never repeating myself creatively. This was a pretty big departure from what I normally do, but I'm beyond stoked with the result and I REALLY hope you are too! My 4th record with Bright Lights and definitely a personal favorite, "Runaway" pulls influence from lots of different genres: from trap to pop to experimental dance. Heather and I wanted to go against the grain, but maintain familiarity and musicality; we hope you think we succeeded. BUT, most importantly, we hope you go absolutely apeshit wild while listening to this, the same way we do ;) 

Much Love,

- Justin

tracks.description:
It would mean a TON to us if you could support the whole EP Here: bit.ly/AliveAgainEP_iT

The Alive Again EP tries something different; it‚Äôs my effort to highlight elements of musical composition in a genre that too often prioritizes ‚Äúcool‚Äù or ‚Äúcatchy‚Äù sounds over musicality. Each version of Alive Again was created with different production techniques, different song-writing styles and thus, each strives to invoke a unique emotional response. We listen to different genres of music depending on our states of mind, so I wanted people to enjoy the song behind Alive Again across multiple moods. Whether you‚Äôre feeling energetic, chill, or need a dose of vulnerability, there‚Äôs always a version to listen to.

I‚Äôm looking forward to following this format for a lot of my future releases. Since my early mashup days I‚Äôve always been fascinated by combinations, how different elements of different things could work together to create something new. The Alive Again EP is the evolution of that fascination that I have with sound. The concept of that in literature is called intertextuality - the idea that every creative concept is influenced by a variety of creative predecessors. I‚Äôm using it as a framework for everything I make moving forward, taking bits and pieces of musical influence from lots of different genres and injecting it in dance music.

More specifically to the Alive Again project, it was an honor to work with Emma Hewitt, as her voice has perfectly complimented some of the most beautiful dance records of our time. Her haunting tone really completes the soundscape of Alive Again, pulling heart strings and effortlessly enveloping listeners in the euphoric atmosphere of the record. I've always viewed myself as a musician first, a producer second, and a performer third; this is the beginning of a new chapter for me, where I'll be doing more projects that showcase musicianship over anything else :)
tracks.title: Alive Again (feat. Emma Hewitt) [Experimental Mix]

tracks.description:
Cat"a*clasm\ N. A breaking asunder; a violent disruption.

Buy on iTunes: bit.ly/CataclasmiTunes
Watch the mini documentary: bit.ly/MakingOfCataclasm
Photography by Dustin Hollywood

And I Can See Your Blood Flow.

I'm not sure when it started, but for a long time now I've had this reoccurring daydream where I walk outside my house, look upwards, and start to slowly float towards the sky. Suspended in the air, rising up, the people and buildings on the ground getting smaller and smaller... It has always given me this very unique feeling that I can't pin down; Almost like a nostalgia for something that hasn't happened yet. It's poetic. Profound. My pulse quickens, I get this invigorating feeling of moving on to another world. It's almost a sort of "L'appel Du Vide." Suddenly nothing else matters. I close my eyes and feel absolute peace.

Where am I going? What am I escaping? What awaits me?

I'm not sure where this single came from inside of me, but I know it has to do with that image. The entire time I was writing, recording and producing this, I felt it. It doesn't have specified verses and choruses, it floats from movement to movement, slowly evolving and growing. I wanted it to be a journey. Every time I listen to it, even now, I feel I'm getting a glimpse into that other world. The clouds are parting, I'm venturing into the void. I hope that, in some small way, it can make you feel the same way.
tracks.title: Rising, Rising

Linked by the spirit of evasion and spiritual elevation, these songs find their roots from the band's time into the wild. Fans can get an early preview of the mix compilation album by downloading the minimix for free in collaboration with cloud-based file service WeTransfer

Premiered at Ultra during Hardwell‚Äôs main stage headline set, ‚ÄòSurvivors‚Äô with long withstanding label mate Dannic, has been sending fans into overdrive ever since the ID surfaced online, with Revealed Volume 6 proving to be the perfect home to showcase what is surely set to be one of the trademark tracks of the year, thanks to a feature spot from rising vocalist and ‚ÄòUnited We Are‚Äô collaborator Haris. In addition to this, an exclusive W&W remix of Hardwell featuring Mr. Probz‚Äôs ‚ÄòBirds Fly‚Äô will be providing a sneak peek into a very special project due later in the year, whilst Hardwell and Wiwek‚Äôs ‚ÄòChameleon‚Äô will be reborn into an instrumental edit especially for the release. 

As Revealed continues on its dominance of the live event landscape, from the label‚Äôs opening parties out at Ushua√Øa Ibiza (as well as Hardwell‚Äôs Carnival also at Ushua√Øa Ibiza for 2015), over to their approaching Tomorrowland arena hosting and stopping off at Creamfields UK along the way, expect music from Kill The Buzz, Thomas Newson and Lucky Date, over to Row Rocka, JAGGS and Maddix, no genre is left untouched with only the label‚Äôs prime selections of progressive house, techno-tinged bass beats and heavier trance influences, make sure you get your hands on the next chapter of  the Revealed story with Hardwell Presents Revealed Volume 6.

THE ONLY way you will ever get this song will be if you buy the Vinyl Record on April 19th (well sort of...also coming out on iTunes April 29th), which happens to be National Record Stay day as Adventure Club attempts to save the Vinyl Record Business with a very limited edition Vinyl release that will include this remix on it as well as some other exclusives...




Quickie from us: Well we love Adventure club and have admired them for a long time. the guys are personable, make great music and are pretty good looking... In many ways we feel we are the same haha jokes, but Adventure were one of the few artists who reached out to us when we started and were cool and supported our music, so when they hit us up about remixing Wonder our fav track off their last album we couldn't resist, that and we want to collab with them so we really had no other option. That said, we think the remix turned out great, we actually see a little bits of our previous work in it, little nods to Around us and Julian. In the end we hope we did the track justice infusing it with a tasteful amount of uptempo progressive house while still remaining true to our style."

Quickie from Adventure Club: "The Chainsmokers are like a better version of us... With their bigger dee's, better hair, and  they make way more intelligent conversation and can easily out drink us on their worst day, We love them'

Michael Calfan - Treasured Soul is out now on Beatport! Full Beatport proceeds will be donated to support the fight against Ebola. Get your copy on iTunes: http://smarturl.it/Treasured_Soul

The Treasured Soul Project
While feedback from dance floors and airwaves increased, ‚ÄòTreasured Soul‚Äô gained momentum, resulting in a campaign lovingly called ‚ÄòThe Treasured Soul Project‚Äô. Going to Michael Calfan‚Äôs website the audience can sign up itself and their loved ones, giving them the chance to win special goodie packages from Michael Calfan and Spinnin‚Äô Records. Being able to literally share your love with a treasured soul, the track has grown a life beyond the music, touching hearts all over the world.

In the wake of this moment Michael Calfan also decided to donate all proceedings from Treasured Soul to a good cause. With ebola threatening so many lives at the moment, the French producer agreed with Spinnin‚Äô Records to make the fight against this disease the key priority surrounding the release of Treasured Soul.

And so, here it is. A highly anticipated track, one of the most striking dance records of 2014, spreading the love on multiple levels. How about that for a holiday spirit?  Michael Calfan makes sure it‚Äôs all good this year.

tracks.description:
Happy New Year everyone!! To kick 2015 off with a bang we decided to finally release our ZHU - Faded remix with @Moiez-babar as a free download!! We want to thank everyone who supported our previous remix of @Goldroom - "Till Sunrise" which peaked at #2 on Hype Machine last week! So unexpected but amazing to see people appreciating some of our experimental stuff. We feel Faded is the precursor to "Till Sunrise" as far as the events of a night unfolding, from that late night phone call until sunrise the next morning. We went for a similar uplifting euphoric feeling but with a bit more energy on this one. We loved the original Faded which was very sexy and dark but with this one we wanted to capture a slightly different perspective on that late night phone call and give the song a whole new life. Hope you guys enjoy this tune and stay tuned for the next one coming soon =)

P.S. We are heavily contemplating releasing an instrumental version with a slightly different breakdown and new melody break. If you guys think its a good idea please leave us a comment =)

cover: that late night moment after the party when you are in the cab, faded, looking out the rain drop covered window, blurred city lights pass you by as you contemplate making that call‚Ä¶.
tracks.title: ZHU - Faded (Mysto & Pizzi X Moiez Remix)

tracks.description:
It would mean a TON to us if you could support the whole EP Here: bit.ly/AliveAgainEP_iT

The Alive Again EP tries something different; it‚Äôs my effort to highlight elements of musical composition in a genre that too often prioritizes ‚Äúcool‚Äù or ‚Äúcatchy‚Äù sounds over musicality. Each version of Alive Again was created with different production techniques, different song-writing styles and thus, each strives to invoke a unique emotional response. We listen to different genres of music depending on our states of mind, so I wanted people to enjoy the song behind Alive Again across multiple moods. Whether you‚Äôre feeling energetic, chill, or need a dose of vulnerability, there‚Äôs always a version to listen to.

I‚Äôm looking forward to following this format for a lot of my future releases. Since my early mashup days I‚Äôve always been fascinated by combinations, how different elements of different things could work together to create something new. The Alive Again EP is the evolution of that fascination that I have with sound. The concept of that in literature is called intertextuality - the idea that every creative concept is influenced by a variety of creative predecessors. I‚Äôm using it as a framework for everything I make moving forward, taking bits and pieces of musical influence from lots of different genres and injecting it in dance music.

More specifically to the Alive Again project, it was an honor to work with Emma Hewitt, as her voice has perfectly complimented some of the most beautiful dance records of our time. Her haunting tone really completes the soundscape of Alive Again, pulling heart strings and effortlessly enveloping listeners in the euphoric atmosphere of the record. I've always viewed myself as a musician first, a producer second, and a performer third; this is the beginning of a new chapter for me, where I'll be doing more projects that showcase musicianship over anything else :)

tracks.description:
WE HOPE YOU ENJOY THIS SONG RESPONSIBLY... ;)

Buy on iTunes: www.smarturl.it/bouquet

Stream on Spotify: http://smarturl.it/StreamBouquet

Music Video:
COMING SOON

----

So what happens when 2 New Yorkers and 2 Texan's get together... Actually that sounds like it would be some political debate, but in this case fucking great progressive House!

So basically Tritonal hit us up maybe 5 months ago about working together on a track! We had always been HUGE fans of their work and literally the same day we were messing around with this Emily Warren Vocal. Tritonal sent over this demo idea and it was so dope! Over the next couple months we tweaked it and eventually arrived at a perfect blend of both our styles. Hats off to Chad and Dave though, such legends, and unbelieveable producers... you think you know about sound design, take a seat cause these dudes will fuck your world up! Nevertheless, in the end we wound up with a beautiful progressive track with an incredible vocal that will get stuck in your head instantly! Literally Emily is one of the best writers out there right now! AND we are all so proud to give you this track! SO PLEASE go out share the song, buy the song, and have a great time with it!

OH and the music video we just filmed is bloody hysterical and we cannot wait to share it!

TRITONAL:
@TRITONALMUSIC
https://twitter.com/Tritonal

EMILY WARREN
https://twitter.com/emilywarrennnn

FUN REAL FACTS
1) We never met Tritonal before this song was finished
2) Both the guys in Tritonal are happily married!
3) Alex looks better than Chad in spandex
4) When Chad from Tritonal is happy he spins in circles

Get the bundle: http://www.smarturl.it/bouquet

Stream: http://smarturl.it/StreamBouquet

Music Video:
COMING SOON

----

This is probably one of the most challenging songs we have ever done. We have legitimately been working on this track for over a year and probably made about 75 completely different versions of it. It was really challenging because the and message is so emotional and raw and we are also from new york so we literally stressed out about every inch of this song. Make it dance, keep it mellow, live instrumentals only, add some tropical vibes, go full progressive, literally we did everything and got super in our heads until our computer crashed and we lost everything... which turned out to be a blessing because when we went back into the project it all flowed out exactly how we wanted it. We have to give a lot of credit though to the writer of this amazing track Brittany who literally poured her soul out on this song she wrote and its beautiful. This just has all the feels of a classic Chainsmoker song so we hope you enjoy it! and the vocal by Victoria Zaro is amazing! We have some other exciting stuff in the works with her!

Note from us: even though you might not be from nyc or have ever been its not about nyc... so dont get hung up on that!

FUN REAL FACTS
1) 100 versions of this song were made 
2) First place we ever played this song was in Boston, sort of ironic
3) Mets clinched the world series same week we are releasing this! GO METS!
4) This is one of the first demos we ever received when we signed to our first major
5) If you lift a kangaroo‚Äôs tail off the ground it can‚Äôt hop.

Hardwell - United We Are (Album) ‚Üí http://bit.ly/UNITEDWEARE

Hardwell feat. Matthew Koma - Dare You (Radio Edit)
OUT NOW! http://bit.ly/DareYou-iTunes

Recently crowned DJ Mag Top 100 #1 Hardwell is not resting on any laurels past this undeniable career landmark. He returns alongside North American songsmith Matthew Koma, beckoning a new direction from the Dutch icon and his peak time powerhouse now found at Revealed Recordings. Premiered during the sold-out edition of Hardwell Presents Revealed at this year's ADE with a special live appearance from Koma himself, the infamous American songwriter behind 'Years' and 'Calling (Lose My Mind)' unites with the recently crowned number one DJ in the world for a definitive vocal club anthem of mass appeal. This highly anticipated vocal record follows up from Hardwell's scorching festival anthem 'Never Say Goodbye', a collaboration with leading Dutch talent Dyro and Bright Lights (aka Heather Bright), and shows a new and melodically refined direction for Hardwell's own peak time aptitude. Interject Koma's on-point songwriting and 'Dare You' marks an unsuspecting yet spectacular display of radio-friendly club fuel that is set in motion another year of domination from this new age Dutch heavyweight.

Dutch DJ & Producer duo, Bassjackers, are set to drop their newest club-banging hit record ‚ÄúLIKE THAT‚Äù on August 18th on Belgian legends Dimitri Vegas & Like Mike‚Äôs SMASH THE HOUSE imprint. 

During last month‚Äôs hugely successful Tomorrowland festivals, it seemed like there was one new track that was getting everyone buzzing. Receiving main stage play on both weekends from Dimitri Vegas & Like Mike, Hardwell, Nicky Romero & Martin Garrix, to name a few ‚ÄúLike That‚Äù quickly became an internet hype and topped the 1001 Tracklist ‚Äúmost heard‚Äù list from the festival. The track, today officially premiered via the below soundcloud link, features a signature high energy Bassjackers drop that is best suited for exactly that stage 

2014 was already a huge highlight reel for Marlon Flohr & Ralph van Hilst - collectively known as Bassjackers. It started out with the monstrous track ‚ÄúCrackin‚Äô ‚Äú (Martin Garrix edit) which topped all the club play charts for much of January & February and is still played by many major name artists. This was soon followed by a collab with LA based DJ MAKJ and the track ‚ÄúDERP‚Äù which went on to chart officially in the US Billbaord Dance top 20. The summer also saw a collab release on Revealed with up coming DJ Kenneth G, ‚ÄúRAMPAGE‚Äù which was first debuted during Hardwell‚Äôs closing set @ Ultra 2014.

Current world #1 DJ Hardwell has had an extraordinary 2014. From continuing to rule supreme over the dance music world, reeling off top-charting hit after hit with epic releases such as ‚ÄòDare You‚Äô, ‚ÄòEverybody Is In The Place‚Äô, the iconic Dutch producer now delivers the newest single ‚ÄòYoung Again‚Äô, from his forthcoming debut album, which is also equipped to hit a high note amongst the charts. Always one to nurture the brightest talents in the industry, Hardwell has enlisted British vocalist Chris Jones, to add a raw, rock-orientated tone, to his euphoric, soaring melodies.
Powered with emotion, ‚ÄòYoung Again‚Äô is a merger of genre-bending bliss, fusing rootsy, electro-acoustic guitar strings with Jones‚Äôs powerful vocals that command attention the second the track begins, a new anthem is truly unleashed. Questioning ‚ÄúWill We Ever Feel Young Again?‚Äù, as the track switches between towering club beats and dominant drops, key chords pound beneath the catchy melody, accumulating in a vocal-driven club stormer with mass appeal.  
Highlighting Hardwell‚Äôs sheer versatility by stepping out of the traditional, progressive-house blueprint and daring to be different, by not being pinned down to a specific strain of dance music and finding inspiration all around him, ‚ÄòYoung Again‚Äô is an infectious record readied to dominate the charts and one that is setting up the imminent release of his new artist album very nicely!

WATCH THE OFFICIAL VIDEO STARRING CHARLIE SHEEN & JEAN-CLAUDE VAN DAMME + FIND OUT WHERE TO GET THE SONG WORLDWIDE ON THIS EXCLUSIVE APP PAGE---> http://thehum.world/buy

Premiered during the formidable duo‚Äôs record breaking Tomorrowland headline set, and one of the standout records of this years Miami Ultra Music Festival, Dimitri Vegas & Like Mike alongside Turkish powerhouse producer Ummet Ozcan have penned an undisputable future classic with ‚ÄòThe Hum‚Äô.

The track has been an untitled fan favourite ID for months thanks to it‚Äôs roaring presence and ability to unite fans in their packs. The Belgian brothers have finally decided to release this clubland scaling hit under the title ‚ÄòThe Hum‚Äô following its explosive inclusion in their big surprise 3 Are Legend appearance, alongside their musical brother Steve Aoki, at Ultra Music Festival in Miami. The track had the Miami crowd primed and ready setting the tone for one of the most exhilarating sets of the entire weekend.
 
Offering up undeniable party chaos, the tracks popularity has swarmed to become something of a breakout moment at recent Dimitri Vegas & Like Mike shows with hundreds of thousands of fans humming along in unison; it created one of the defining moments of the Tomorrowland tenth anniversary celebrations.

Signifying bold connotations of instilling rhythm and psyching up the audience the collective trio usher in fresh ideas for a new year as ‚ÄòThe Hum‚Äô erupts with headline-ready explosions.
tracks.title: Dimitri Vegas & Like Mike vs Ummet Ozcan - The Hum - BEATPORT #1

When it comes to stellar collaborations, it doesn‚Äôt get much bigger than this. ‚ÄòDamn‚Äô is the work of electro house legend Chuckie and Spanish star Albert Neve, a duo who previously set the scene on fire with their remix of Ambush & DJ Obek‚Äôs ‚ÄòCraissy‚Äô back in 2012. Their debut original collaboration is more of the same, a devastating electro anthem that is perfectly poised to light up dance floors and raise the roof at venues across the planet. 

Built around a ‚Äò90s-esque synth riff that dances around the track from the off, where ‚ÄòDAMN‚Äô really shines is in how these guys have taken their respective experience, and used it to create something that combines old-school cues with modern electro energy. Both Chuckie and Albert have been part of the dance music scene for a number of years, but their ability to remain ahead of the curve while making subtle nods to their roots is clear to see in ‚ÄòDamn‚Äô. From the pounding percussion, to the bouncy drops, through to the quirky vocal shouts, ‚ÄòDamn‚Äô is also a crowd-friendly anthem that should see it go down a storm in DJ sets, with plenty of support from the big guns already under its belt.

tracks.description:
THE ONLY way you will ever get this song will be if you buy the Vinyl Record on April 19th (well sort of...also coming out on iTunes April 29th), which happens to be National Record Stay day as Adventure Club attempts to save the Vinyl Record Business with a very limited edition Vinyl release that will include this remix on it as well as some other exclusives...




Quickie from us: Well we love Adventure club and have admired them for a long time. the guys are personable, make great music and are pretty good looking... In many ways we feel we are the same haha jokes, but Adventure were one of the few artists who reached out to us when we started and were cool and supported our music, so when they hit us up about remixing Wonder our fav track off their last album we couldn't resist, that and we want to collab with them so we really had no other option. That said, we think the remix turned out great, we actually see a little bits of our previous work in it, little nods to Around us and Julian. In the end we hope we did the track justice infusing it with a tasteful amount of uptempo progressive house while still remaining true to our style."

Quickie from Adventure Club: "The Chainsmokers are like a better version of us... With their bigger dee's, better hair, and  they make way more intelligent conversation and can easily out drink us on their worst day, We love them'

SUPPORT THE ORIGINAL ARTIST:
@AdventureClub

www.twitter.com/adventuredub

The Kite String Tangle
www.facebook.com/thekitestringtangle
www.soundcloud.com/thekitestringtangle

FUN FACT(s):
1) If Alex and Drew fought Leighton and Christian, Alex and Drew would win
2) If The Chainsmokers and Adventure club were raffled off in a auction to raise money, The Chainsmokers would bring in more money
3) One time The Chainsmokers lent Adventure club money cause they are poor, and didnt even ask for the money back when they got rich...
4) Adventure Club may appear to be more popular numerically across all social media platforms but thats really some illuminati shit...
5) We Love Adventure Club very much :)
